[div class=p 
	"It is available as a stand-alone program here:
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[a href=http://bisqwit.iki.fi/source/animmerger.html rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"http://bisqwit.iki.fi/source/animmerger.html
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"In the past, it used to be a direct patch to the emulators.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This was done because the emulator could directly give information regarding the background layers' scrolling position.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Now, as a stand-alone program, global scrolling has to be deduced algorithmically from the image contents. It is a bit slower, but it no longer depends on the emulator.
	$LF
]div
